18:08.800 --> 18:10.720
Science Fiction and Fantasy author Pierce Anthony

18:10.720 --> 18:12.980
has been writing in these genres since the mid-60s.

18:13.320 --> 18:16.420
Anthony's apparent production was fairly low until 1977

18:16.740 --> 18:19.360
when his work began appearing with increasing frequency.

18:19.940 --> 18:23.480
Right. Since that apparently sudden explosion of effort in 1977,

18:23.480 --> 18:26.440
some 18 Anthony volumes have appeared in print for the first time.

18:26.640 --> 18:29.420
But Anthony did not suddenly begin writing in a brisk or pace.

18:29.780 --> 18:32.560
He told us that he had been blacklisted by the publishing industry

18:32.560 --> 18:35.780
in the early 70s because he had insisted on being paid fairly

18:35.780 --> 18:37.680
for his first published novel, Thone.

18:38.220 --> 18:40.360
The explosion of his works in print in 1977

18:40.360 --> 18:42.840
was a result of his overcoming the blacklisting.

18:43.000 --> 18:43.800
Here Anthony explains.

18:54.180 --> 18:58.100
I'll say 50% of my output was getting into print.

18:58.680 --> 19:00.340
But when I finally got through that,

19:00.500 --> 19:02.500
I finally became apparent to some of these publishers

19:03.060 --> 19:06.220
that I was the one that was right, you see.

19:07.920 --> 19:10.220
See, the word was being spread by the blacklisters

19:10.220 --> 19:12.400
how difficult a writer I was to deal with

19:12.400 --> 19:14.420
and don't deal with this guy and so on.

19:14.480 --> 19:15.300
It's just nothing but trouble.

19:16.920 --> 19:19.340
When I finally, when that passed,

19:19.420 --> 19:21.540
and I got to working with editors who knew me personally

19:21.540 --> 19:26.500
and knew what to sell, then I could sell everything I wrote.

19:27.240 --> 19:28.920
So now you're seeing everything I write

19:28.920 --> 19:30.180
and it looks like an explosion,

19:30.340 --> 19:32.680
but I always was writing at that pace.

19:33.320 --> 19:34.760
I just couldn't get it into print.

19:35.300 --> 19:37.120
Peer's Anthony is actually a known diploma

19:37.120 --> 19:40.000
utilizing only the author's first and second names.

19:40.500 --> 19:42.480
When we asked Anthony why he uses a pen name,

19:42.640 --> 19:44.660
we found out it's due to some long-range planning.

19:45.420 --> 19:48.540
I decided on that before I ever sold a thing

19:49.360 --> 19:51.360
and said, supposing I write,

19:51.640 --> 19:53.380
and just supposing I'm successful

19:53.380 --> 19:56.380
and just supposing I get to be famous.

19:56.840 --> 19:59.280
Oh, this was an awful lot of supposing.

20:00.000 --> 20:01.920
I mean, I hadn't even sold anything.

20:02.380 --> 20:03.740
I'd been trying for several years and hadn't.

20:04.900 --> 20:07.900
I've heard about writers such as John D. McDonald,

20:08.460 --> 20:09.340
a mystery writer,

20:10.400 --> 20:12.140
and he had to move several times

20:12.140 --> 20:14.900
because people would come in and just drop in.

20:15.020 --> 20:17.380
They would assume that he had nothing better to do

20:17.380 --> 20:19.920
than to talk with every fan that dropped in on his address.

20:20.600 --> 20:22.960
And so he would have to move so his address would be lost.

20:23.060 --> 20:24.560
It would take him two or three years to find him

20:24.560 --> 20:25.920
and then they'd take up his time again.

20:26.440 --> 20:30.100
Why have this happened to me if I ever get that well known?

20:30.900 --> 20:33.100
The answer was to use the pen name.

20:34.140 --> 20:37.120
So I set up with a pen name from the outset

20:37.120 --> 20:39.520
and it has protected me.

20:39.600 --> 20:40.620
I get a lot of fan mail.

20:40.860 --> 20:41.780
It goes through the publisher.

20:42.260 --> 20:44.260
I don't get many people dropping in on me

20:44.260 --> 20:45.340
because they can't find me.

20:45.600 --> 20:46.700
They can look up in the phone book.

20:47.180 --> 20:49.920
I don't know, maybe there's somebody locally called Anthony

20:49.920 --> 20:51.900
that keeps getting people dropping in on him.

20:52.080 --> 20:53.460
It's not me, you see.

20:54.440 --> 20:56.120
So I have protected myself.

20:56.320 --> 20:58.580
If I want someone to know who I am, I can tell them.

20:59.160 --> 21:01.260
But the stranger that just says,

21:01.340 --> 21:03.500
hey, gee, there's this writer, I think I'll drop in on him,

21:03.720 --> 21:05.160
he is unable to find me.

21:05.680 --> 21:09.680
And so now I'm beginning to approach the sort of success

21:10.600 --> 21:13.280
that the pseudonym was prepared for.

21:13.280 --> 21:15.180
I really never thought I would get there.

21:15.280 --> 21:16.660
It was just saying, suppose,

21:17.800 --> 21:19.840
and I planned well, I'm having more success

21:19.840 --> 21:21.580
than I really believed I would have.

21:21.980 --> 21:25.120
And now my pen name is serving to protect me,

21:25.720 --> 21:27.120
to protect my time, really.

21:27.660 --> 21:29.120
Not that I'm talking with people,

21:29.800 --> 21:31.820
but you know, there would be a lot of people

21:31.820 --> 21:32.900
that would just like to come.

21:33.360 --> 21:35.360
If there's a writer there, they won't even have read

21:35.360 --> 21:36.340
anything by that author.

21:36.480 --> 21:38.160
They say, gee, that's a writer, I'll go talk to him.

21:38.640 --> 21:40.260
But I don't need that sort of thing.

21:40.260 --> 21:43.080
I'm willing to talk to people that have read my works,

21:43.340 --> 21:45.800
that want to talk to me, ask me intelligent questions,

21:46.500 --> 21:47.940
that people more like you.

21:48.060 --> 21:51.040
You see, I'm not willing to talk to the man off the street.

21:51.480 --> 21:53.040
He just has heard that I'm a writer.

21:53.440 --> 21:56.920
He doesn't even know what I'm writing about.

21:57.560 --> 21:58.840
But just, if there's a writer,

21:59.020 --> 22:01.840
he just wants to go and talk to him and take up his time.

22:03.800 --> 22:04.940
So that's the reason.

22:05.060 --> 22:07.240
Again, a rather commercial reason, if you will.

22:09.580 --> 22:11.400
But I think it's factored.

22:12.420 --> 22:14.540
We'll have more about Piers Anthony on our next show.

